The paper deals with graph and digraph coloring, and the existence of properly colored cycles. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) in constructing the graphs. The use of recursive constructions suggests that the paper may also involve data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds on the minimum monochromatic degree, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
